---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import RegistrationForm from '../components/RegistrationForm.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Get Involved — Spotsylvania RFC"
  description="Find your role at Spotsylvania RFC. Players, parents, coaches, volunteers, referees, sponsors, and supporters are all needed to build this club."
  ogTitle="Get Involved — Spotsylvania RFC"
  ogDescription="Every role matters. Join the founding list and tell us how you want to help build Spotsylvania RFC."
>
  <Header />

  <main id="main-content">

    <div class="ph-outer">
      <div class="ph-inner">
        <p class="section-label">Get Involved</p>
        <h1 class="section-title">Every role <em>matters.</em></h1>
        <p class="section-body">
          A rugby club is not built by players alone. It takes coaches, parents, volunteers,
          referees, sponsors, and supporters who are willing to step forward before the club
          exists. If any of that sounds like you, your name belongs on the founding list.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="section">
      <p class="section-label">Roles</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">How you can <em>help.</em></h2>
      <p class="section-body">
        No commitment is required at this stage. Joining the founding list tells us who you are
        and how you might like to be involved. That information shapes what the first season looks
        like and who we need to reach next.
      </p>

      <div class="role-grid">

        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="role-title">Player</div>
          <p>
            Youth or adult. No experience required. The founding list is the first step — sessions
            and formats will be confirmed once we have a clear picture of numbers, ages, and
            interest level.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="role-title">Parent &amp; Family</div>
          <p>
            Parents are essential to a youth programme. Managing, coordinating, chaperoning,
            driving, and showing up consistently — those contributions are what keep a youth club
            running. Rugby experience is not required.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="role-title">Coach</div>
          <p>
            We need coaches at all levels. Rugby coaching experience is welcome but not
            required — coaches from other sports bring real skills. Training and certification
            support will be available. What matters most is willingness and patience.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="role-title">Volunteer</div>
          <p>
            Field setup, event coordination, communications, administration — there is no shortage
            of work in a founding club. Volunteers make everything possible. An hour here and
            there adds up significantly.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="role-title">Referee</div>
          <p>
            Referees are one of the hardest things for a new club to develop. If you are
            interested in officiating, USA Rugby offers referee development courses. We would like
            to know you now and support you through the process.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="role-title">Sponsor</div>
          <p>
            Local businesses that support the club at founding help determine what the first
            season looks like. Kit, field costs, equipment, and insurance all require funding.
            Sponsorship discussions are welcome at any stage of this process.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="role-title">School Contact</div>
          <p>
            Teachers, administrators, and PE staff who can open doors to school sessions, fields,
            and students are among the most valuable contacts a founding programme can have. If
            you work in education in Spotsylvania, we want to hear from you.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="role-card">
          <div class="role-title">Supporter</div>
          <p>
            Not ready to commit to a specific role but want to see this happen? That counts. Put
            your name down. Knowing that people are watching and want this to work is meaningful
            and we will keep you informed as the club develops.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <RegistrationForm />
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .ph-outer {
    background: var(--green);
    padding: 0 24px;
  }

  .ph-inner {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: calc(var(--section-pad-v) + 52px) 0 var(--section-pad-v);
  }

  .ph-outer .section-label { color: var(--gold); }
  .ph-outer .section-title { color: var(--cream); }
  .ph-outer .section-title em { color: var(--gold); }
  .ph-outer .section-body { color: rgba(246, 242, 230, 0.75); margin-bottom: 0; }

  .role-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: 32px;
    margin-top: 48px;
  }

  .role-card {
    border-top: 3px solid var(--gold);
    padding-top: 20px;
  }

  .role-title {
    font-family: 'Oswald', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .role-card p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
